y reminder that a rich life is a life rich in thought.Today, when even the humanities are often defended only for their economic or political usefulness, Hitz says our intellectual lives are valuable not despite but because of their practical uselessness. And while anyone can have an intellectual life, she encourages academics in particular to get back in touch with the desire to learn for its own sake, and calls on universities to return to the person-to-person transmission of the habits of mind and heart that bring out the best in us.Reminding us of who we once were and who we might become, Lost in Thought is a moving account of why renewing our inner lives is fundamental to preserving our humanity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aIntellectual life. 0aThought and thinking. 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh  aCultivating Humanity.  aExcellent Sheep.  aFareed Zakaria.  aIn Defense of Liberal Education.  aMartha Nussbaum.  aMatthew Crawford.  aNot for Profit.  aShop Class as Soulcraft.  aWilliam Deresiewicz.  aacademic memoir.  abooks for book lovers.  acritique of education.  agifts for students.  ainspirational books for students.  aintellectual pursuits.  alay intellectuals.  alife of the mind.  alove of learning.  amemoir of education.  apurpose of education.  auses of education.  avalue of education.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020 Englishz978311070482208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2020z9783110704648oZDB-23-DPH08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPUP eBook-Package